FAIRBANKS, AK: A new scientific synthesis suggests a gradual, prolonged release of greenhouse gases from permafrost soils in Arctic and sub-Arctic regions, which may afford society more time to adapt to environmental changes, say scientists in a paper published in&nbsp; 
<em>Nature</em>....&nbsp;
<br> 
<br> This press release discusses findings from a study,&nbsp; 
<a href="http://www.nature.com/nature/journal/v520/n7546/full/nature14338.html">Climate change and the permafrost carbon feedback</a>, from the project,&nbsp; 
<a href="https://nccwsc.usgs.gov/display-project/4f831626e4b0e84f6086809b/503faaa3e4b09851b69ab403">Development and Application of an Integrated Ecosystem Model for Alaska</a>.&nbsp;

